# Keep the host's installed deps and build artifacts OUT of the Docker build
# context. The Dockerfiles run their own `pnpm install` inside the image; copying
# the host node_modules over that clean install leaves dangling pnpm symlinks
# (host and container resolve slightly different peer hashes) and breaks the
# in-image TypeScript build. Excluding them also shrinks the context a lot.
**/node_modules
node_modules

# Build outputs (regenerated inside the image)
**/dist
**/.next
apps/desktop/release
packages/shared/dist

# VCS / local tooling
.git
.gitignore
.husky

# Secrets & local env (compose injects env via `environment:`)
.env
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Misc
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
.vscode
.idea
